metadata.name: "ŌMUKADE"
metadata.description:
"Ōmukade"

inspired by the Japanese mythology "Ōmukade"

The Ōmukade is a giant man-eating centipede that lives in the mountains. While it eats humans, the Ōmukade has a weakness to human saliva.

Ōmukade are extremely rare. When they are seen, they pose a threat to all in the area. Throughout history, the responsibility of exterminating these monsters has fallen on the shoulders of brave warriors.
